{
  "texts": [
    "They enable models to focus on relevant information across time and space.",
    "In ecology, attention mechanisms can be applied to analyze species distribution patterns influenced by various environmental factors.Graph Neural Networks (GNNs): Modeling Ecological Networks: GNNs are vital in ecology for modeling complex ecological networks, such as food webs, mutualistic interactions, or habitat connectivity.",
    "They allow researchers to understand the structure and dynamics of ecosystems and predict the consequences of species loss or habitat fragmentation.Deep Reinforcement Learning (DRL): Optimizing Decision-Making: DRL techniques can optimize decision-making processes in climate adaptation and ecosystem management.",
    "For example, they can be used to find optimal resource allocation strategies for conservation efforts or determine the best time for planting crops based on climate conditions.",
    "Time-Series Forecasting: Predictive Modeling: Deep learning models like Prophet or WaveNet are applied to climate and ecological time-series data for accurate forecasting."
  ]
}